      <section eId="sec_44_6_22">
        <num>44-6-22</num>
        <content>
          <p>An absolute estate may be created to commence in the future, and the fee may be in abeyance without detriment to the rights of subsequent remainders. A fee may be limited upon a fee, either by deed or will, where the plain intention of the grantor or testator requires it and no other rule of law is violated thereby.</p>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 2227; Code 1868, § 2221; Code 1873, § 2247; Code 1882, § 2247; Civil Code 1895, § 3082; Civil Code 1910, § 3658; Code 1933, § 85-502.)</p>
        </content>
